music. Listeners will hear his compositions afresh, and scholars will find new results of research and analysis and new avenues for discovery. Topics include Beethoven's cultural milieu, his personal life, his friends, his publishers, his instruments, his working methods, his own handwritten scores, and, of course, his music. Many works are carefully discussed and explained in ways that reveal fascinating and previously unknown aspects of compositions that we thought we knew well. A landmark publication for all who admire some of the greatest music of our civilization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / Individual Composer & Musician.2bisacsh  aBeethoven's music.  aLudwig van Beethoven.  acomposer's legacy.  amusic history.  amusic interpretation.  amusical analysis.  amusical evolution.  amusicology.1 aAdolphe, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbrecht, Theodore, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarry, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonds, Mark Evan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurnham, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuurman, Erica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGosman, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, David Wyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKinderman, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKitchen, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKramer, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabula